-- MOVES-Nomura names new head of investment banking in Indonesia -memo
-- 
-- Thu Sep 18, 2014 02:54AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Sept 18 (Reuters) - Nomura Holdings Inc <8604.t> has named Kartadjaja Intan as its new head of investment banking in Indonesia, the Japan-based firm said in an internal memo seen by Reuters on Thursday.

Intan has worked for Citigroup <C.N> and BNP Paribas <BNPP.PA> and was most recently deputy chief executive of RHB OSK Securities in Indonesia, the memo said.